<h1>Modal with Ember-Forms</h1>

{{#link-to 'component.modal.forms'}}Modal Forms{{/link-to}} takes a special care of managing forms withi modals,
But if you want to use <a href="https://github.com/indexiatech/ember-forms">Ember Forms</a> within modals then read on.

<h2>Demo</h2>

{{#em-modal-emform configName="bs" id="modalf" on-submit="addUser" model=newUser in-async=async}}
    {{#em-modal-title}}
        {{#em-modal-toggler class="close"}}<span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span><span class="sr-only">Close</span>{{/em-modal-toggler}}
        <h4 class="modal-title">Add User</h4>
    {{/em-modal-title}}
    {{#em-modal-body}}
        {{#if async}}
            Submitting, please wait...
        {{else}}
            {{em-input property="name" label="Full Name" placeholder="Enter a name..."}}
            {{em-input property="password" label="Password" placeholder="And password..." type="password"}}
        {{/if}}
    {{/em-modal-body}}
    {{#em-modal-footer}} 
        {{em-form-submit}}
    {{/em-modal-footer}}
{{/em-modal-emform}}

{{#em-modal-toggler modal-id="modalf" class="btn btn-primary" on-toggle='initUser'}}Add User{{/em-modal-toggler}}

<h3>Users</h3>
<p>
<ul>
{{#each model}}
    <li>{{name}}</li>
{{/each}}
</ul>
</p>